History 
Jonathan Bell Lovelace believed that fundamental research is essential to achieving superior long-term investment results. The small company he founded in 1931 has grown into one of the world’s most respected financial institutions.



















Management Team 
Our governance structure is built on the premise that a group of individuals with diverse perspectives can reach better decisions through discussion and debate.



















Company Culture 
In an environment where great ideas are allowed to flourish, our associates are bound by a common purpose and a shared set of values.









Office Locations
News Room












 
















 OUR SERVICES 
 OUR APPROACH 
 OUR COMPANY 








































For more than 80 years, we’ve put investors first.  









The Capital Advantage
Since 1931, Capital Group has been singularly focused on delivering superior, consistent results for long-term investors using high-conviction portfolios, rigorous research and individual accountability.   
Aligned with Investor Success
The Capital SystemSM
Built to Last


















 











  Our Services  










We serve individual investors, financial intermediaries and institutions around the world through a broad range of products and services that include American Funds, one of the largest mutual fund families in the U.S. by assets under management.












  Our Company  










As a private firm with an independent charter, we are focused on doing what’s right for investors over the long term. In offices throughout Asia, Australia, Europe and North America, 7,500 associates make the needs of our investors their top priority every day. 












  News Room  










Visit the news room for our latest news, original research and company facts. You will also find contact information for our global media relations team.













 
 
























































